Here's the recommended approach using `App` lifecycle methods and `Preferences`:

**App.xaml.cs** â€” hook into sleep/resume:

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    protected override void OnSleep()
    {
        // Fires when app goes to background
        MessagingCenter.Send(this, "AppSleep");
    }

    protected override void OnResume()
    {
        // Fires when app returns to foreground
        MessagingCenter.Send(this, "AppResume");
    }
}
```

**NotePage.xaml.cs** â€” save/restore the draft:

```csharp
public partial class NotePage : ContentPage
{
    private const string DraftKey = "NoteDraft";

    public NotePage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        MessagingCenter.Subscribe<App>(this, "AppSleep", _ => SaveDraft());
        MessagingCenter.Subscribe<App>(this, "AppResume", _ => RestoreDraft());

        // Restore on first load too
        RestoreDraft();
    }

    private void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, NoteEditor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    private void RestoreDraft()
    {
        if (Preferences.ContainsKey(DraftKey))
            NoteEditor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
    }

    // Clear draft when the user explicitly saves
    private void OnSaveClicked(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        // ... your save logic ...
        Preferences.Remove(DraftKey);
    }

    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        MessagingCenter.Unsubscribe<App>(this, "AppSleep");
        MessagingCenter.Unsubscribe<App>(this, "AppResume");
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

| Concept | Detail |
|---|---|
| **`OnSleep`/`OnResume`** | App lifecycle hooks â€” fire on background/foreground transitions |
| **`Preferences`** | Simple key-value store, persists across app restarts |
| **`MessagingCenter`** | Decouples `App` from specific pages |
| **Cleanup** | Unsubscribe in `OnDisappearing` to avoid leaks |
| **Clear on save** | Remove the draft when the user intentionally saves |

> **Note:** `MessagingCenter` is deprecated in newer MAUI versions. If you're on .NET 8+, use `WeakReferenceMessenger` from the **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** NuGet package instead â€” same pattern, just swap `MessagingCenter.Send/Subscribe` for `WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send/Register`.
